node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.title: Mexican cartels are recruiting teens on TikTok to smuggle migrants

node.text: Fifty-three years ago, a government commission investigated civil unrest and racial inequality in America. The results from the "Kerner Report" shocked the country but mostly faded into history. The last surviving member, 90-year-old Fred Harris, shares why.

node.title: A 1968 report called out White racism, but history largely forgot it

node.text: The April 12 police killing Anthony Thompson Jr. inside of a bathroom at Knoxville's Austin-East Magnet High School has sparked a wave of protests throughout the city. Thompson is the school's fifth student to die at the hands of gun violence this year, and many in the Black community say they've reached a boiling point. We went to the frontlines of demonstrations to speak with activists, teachers, and residents who say they're committed to calling attention to systemic failures plaguing the Black community in Knoxville.

node.text: During the CNN town hall Wednesday night, President Biden made a number of false and misleading claims, including saying you’re not going to get Covid if you’re vaccinated. Biden’s blanket promises — that vaccinated people are simply “not going to be hospitalized,” “not going to die” and, even with the very contagious Delta variant, “not going to get Covid” — were inaccurate.

node.text:
Ugandan Annet Negesa and Kenyan Maximila Imali both had their Olympic dreams crushed because of rules set by track and field global governing body World Athletics. They are just two – of many – elite women athletes who have been told their natural testosterone levels, if not lowered through medication or surgery, disqualify them from competition at the highest levels of sport. 

Tap the link in our bio for CNN's full report.

Intersex people have natural variations in reproductive anatomy, chromosome patterns or other traits that may not align with typical binary definitions of female or male. These variations are sometimes called differences in sex development, or DSD. It is difficult to estimate how many people have DSD traits many live their entire lives without ever knowing they have one. node.text:
A teenage pilot made an emergency landing on a New Jersey bridge Monday after the aircraft experienced an engine malfunction. Landon Lucas, 18, was flying a banner plane over the New Jersey shoreline when he realized the airbox of his plane was dangling off the spring, preventing a proper flow of fuel on his aircraft. The Federal Aviation Administration confirmed that Lucas was able to land his plane on a bridge on the Route 52 highway near Ocean City, New Jersey. Lucas, who was the sole person on the plane, said he did not suffer any injuries. "There was not a scratch, just traffic," he said.⁠
⁠
(📸: @kr4shorerealestate)

In May, the US Food and Drug Administration expanded the emergency use authorization for Pfizer's Covid-19 vaccine to include people ages 12 to 15. node.text:
The Norwegian women's beach handball team has been fined after players opted to wear shorts instead of bikini bottoms during a European championship game. The European Handball Federation said Monday that it had imposed a fine of $1,766 — $176 for each player — on the team for "improper clothing" in the bronze medal game against Spain on Sunday. Female athletes must wear bikini bottoms with a side width a maximum of 3.9 inches, with a "close fit" and "cut on an upward angle toward the top of the leg," according to International Handball Federation regulations. Meanwhile, men must wear shorts that are "not too baggy" and 10 centimeters above the kneecap. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠
⁠
(📸: Norges Handballforbund/Twitter)

node.text:
Follow ➡️ @cnnclimate ➡️ There are 80 large fires burning across 13 states this week, and the effects of the blazes stretch all the way to the East Coast. Extraordinary plumes of wildfire smoke are reaching so far up into the atmosphere that they are being carried thousands of miles east by high-level winds. The smoke's effect on light causes the sun to look red at sunset as the sky takes on a burnt-orange color, and it also affects air quality. The climate crisis has made deadlier and more destructive wildfires the new normal. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠
⁠
(📸: NASA Modis)
